# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version.
#   See https://github.com/pyenv/pyenv/blob/master/COMMANDS.md#pyenv-version-file
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if used in a multi-platform environment, it may cause problems.
#.venv
#pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock contains the resolved dependencies, and should be versioned.
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock contains the resolved dependencies, and should be versioned.
#pdm.lock

# PEP 582; dependency directory created by pipflow via `pdm install --pep582`
